resources.name: üîß WORKFLOW GUIDE - Read First!
resources.description:
WORKFLOW GUIDE:

üöÄ QUICK START:
1. START HERE: Test service health (this endpoint)
2. Process emails using the 'Process [Type] Email' requests
3. Copy the 'ProcessedEmailId' from the response JSON
4. Paste it into draft generation requests (replace the GUID)
5. View filtered emails to see processed results
6. Generate drafts for emails that require responses

üìã REQUIRED FIELDS:
- ProcessEmailCommand: EmailId, UserId, Subject, From (valid email), To (valid email), Body, ReceivedAt
- GenerateDraftCommand: ProcessedEmailId (GUID from step 2), UserId

üîß TROUBLESHOOTING:
- If you get validation errors, ensure all required fields are present
- For draft generation, you MUST use a ProcessedEmailId from a previously processed email
- Check that email addresses are in valid format (e.g., user@domain.com)
- If filtered emails return empty, it may be a database issue - but email processing and draft generation still work!
- IMPORTANT: Make sure you have 'Base Environment' selected in Insomnia!

üåê ENVIRONMENT SETUP:
- Select 'Base Environment' from the environment dropdown
- Verify these variables are set (without {{ }} in the values):
  * base_url: http://localhost:6006
  * yarp_url: http://localhost:6004
  * processedEmailId: (leave empty initially)
  * draftId: (leave empty initially)

üí° WORKING EXAMPLE:
1. Run 'Process Urgent Email' ‚Üí get ProcessedEmailId (e.g., '2856ad17-e179-417b-9593-fd16b34362ef')
2. Use that ID in 'Generate Draft Response' request
3. See the AI-generated response!

‚ö†Ô∏è NOTE: The database might not persist between container restarts, but the AI processing and draft generation work perfectly!

resources.name: Process Urgent Email
resources.description: Process an urgent server maintenance email

body.text:
{
  "EmailId": "email-001",
  "UserId": "user-123",
  "Subject": "URGENT: Server downtime scheduled for tonight",
  "From": "admin@company.com",
  "To": "team@company.com",
  "Body": "Hi Team,\n\nWe have scheduled a critical server maintenance tonight from 11 PM to 3 AM. Please save your work and log off before 11 PM. This is urgent and cannot be postponed.\n\nThanks,\nIT Admin",
  "ReceivedAt": "2025-06-24T14:30:00Z"
}
